{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17626367","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17626367"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:36:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:36:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17070"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17070","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17070"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.17,0.17,0.21,0.38,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9760"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68967"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9760","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9760"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17070"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54424"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"5267"},{"type":"tags","id":"5270"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22938"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23118"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68967","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/68967"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old woman with acute myeloid leukaemia develops invasive pulmonary aspergillosis. She is started on intravenous amphotericin B.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the mechanism of action of amphotericin B?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Inhibits fungal protein synthesis","Blocks fungal DNA replication","Inhibits ergosterol synthesis","Binds to ergosterol creating membrane pores","Disrupts fungal cell wall synthesis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAmphotericin B works by \u003Cstrong\u003Ebinding to ergosterol creating membrane pores\u003C/strong\u003E in fungal cell membranes. This interaction creates channels that disrupt membrane integrity, leading to leakage of essential ions and metabolites. The resulting loss of cellular contents and osmotic imbalance causes fungal cell death.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibition of fungal protein synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E - This is not a mechanism of action of any current antifungal agents\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocking of fungal DNA replication\u003C/strong\u003E - This is not a mechanism of action of any current antifungal agents\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibition of ergosterol synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes the mechanism of azole antifungals like fluconazole\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDisruption of fungal cell wall synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes the mechanism of echinocandin antifungals like caspofungin\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAmphotericin B\u0027s selective toxicity arises from its higher affinity for ergosterol in fungal membranes compared to cholesterol in human cell membranes. However, some interaction with cholesterol does occur, explaining its significant side effects including nephrotoxicity and infusion reactions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Amphotericin B causes fungal cell death through binding to ergosterol in fungal cell membranes and creating pores.","Ergosterol is a sterol specific to fungal cell membranes, making amphotericin B selectively toxic to fungi.","The main adverse effects of amphotericin B are nephrotoxicity and infusion-related reactions."],"references":["Increases excretion of uric acid -Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54424"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17070"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54424","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/54424"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-10T19:23:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-10T19:24:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9760"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68967"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"created